            "answer_text": " Teri Garr played Roberta Lincoln in the 1968 episode of Star Trek, \u201cAssignment: Earth\u201d (aired March 29, 1968, Season 2, Episode 26). The episode is what\u2019s known as a backdoor pilot, meaning that it\u2019s an episode of one show meant to showcase another, in this case trying to launch a new show Gene Roddenberry planned in case Star Trek didn\u2019t pan out. The episode is a disaster in terms of story. The main characters are sidelined while this new guy, Gary Seven, is working to prevent a nuclear war between the United States and the Soviet Union, all while Roberta is pretty much the know-nothing assistant hired because\u2026 reasons? Teri Garr was not happy with how the entire thing went down, and to this day is reluctant at all to speak about her time on Star Trek. ",
